summary: another renly headcanon (or two) because why not renly didn't learn to swim (canon or modern au) until he was seventeen years...
body:
another renly headcanon (or two)

because why not

renly didn’t learn to swim (canon or modern au) until he was seventeen years old. as a child and through to his early teens, he had nightmares about his parents’ deaths and dreamt about falling into water and drowning. (modern au) robert took him to the beach once when he was six and took him paddling; he fell over and the waves went over his head, and he panicked and cried so much he was sick and refused to go anywhere near water again for years. oberyn taught him in spain when he was seventeen, by basically coaxing him deeper into the sea and teaching him how to do stuff like floating and treading water before moving onto actual swimming.

ALTERNATIVELY;

renly loves the water and was always sneaking out of the house to go to the beach. more than once stannis has caught him coming back at 2am, wet with salt-stiff hair and a towel around his shoulders, blue-lipped and shivering. he has always been obsessed with it; stannis and robert don’t understand, because that’s how their parents died, robert is still wary of ships and boats and stannis only sets foot on them under great sufferance.
